repeat the extraction by boiling with 20 mL of distilled water;
- wash the crucible and the char on the filter with hot distilled water until the filtrate measures approximately 200 mL;
wash the crucible and the char on the filter with hot distilled water until the filtrate measures approximately 200 mL;
- add 7 mL of freshly prepared Bromine Solution;
add 7 mL of freshly prepared Bromine Solution;
- then slowly add 40 mL of Dilute Phosphoric Acid (1 in 2) and boil until starch iodide paper is no longer coloured blue by the vapours;
then slowly add 40 mL of Dilute Phosphoric Acid (1 in 2) and boil until starch iodide paper is no longer coloured blue by the vapours;
- during the boiling add distilled water from time to time, as necessary, to maintain a volume of not less than 200 mL;
during the boiling add distilled water from time to time, as necessary, to maintain a volume of not less than 200 mL;
- wash down the walls of the flask with distilled water, and continue the boiling for 5 minutes;
wash down the walls of the flask with distilled water, and continue the boiling for 5 minutes;
- cool, add 5 mL of Phenol Solution (1 in 20);
cool, add 5 mL of Phenol Solution (1 in 20);
- rinse the walls of the flask, and allow to stand for 5 minutes;
rinse the walls of the flask, and allow to stand for 5 minutes;
- add 2 mL of Dilute Phosphoric Acid (1 in 2) and 5 mL of Potassium Iodide Solution;
add 2 mL of Dilute Phosphoric Acid (1 in 2) and 5 mL of Potassium Iodide Solution;
- titrate immediately with 0.01 N Sodium Thiosulfate, adding 3 mL of Starch Solution as the end-point is approached;
titrate immediately with 0.01 N Sodium Thiosulfate, adding 3 mL of Starch Solution as the end-point is approached;
- perform a blank determination, and make any necessary correction;
